#: index.docbook:3386
msgid "Getting more information"
msgstr "Erhalten von weiterer Information"

#: index.docbook:3391
msgid "Where is the &kde; homepage?"
msgstr "Wo ist die &kde; Homepage?"

#: index.docbook:3394
msgid ""
"The &kde; homepage is located at <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kde.org\">http://www.kde.org</ulink>. If you prefer a local "
"mirror, there are several to choose from. For a current list of web site "
"mirrors sorted by location, please visit <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kde.org/webmirrors.html\">http://www.kde.org/webmirrors.html"
"</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Die Adresse der &kde;-Homepage ist: <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kde.org\">http://www.kde.org</ulink>. Es gibt einige lokale "
"Spiegelserver, die Sie der Hauptseite vorziehen sollten. Sie finden eine "
"aktuelle Liste der Spiegelserver immer unter: <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kde.org/webmirrors.html\">http://www.kde.org/webmirrors.html"
" </ulink>."

#: index.docbook:3404
msgid "Is there a &kde; mailing list?"
msgstr "Gibt es eine &kde; Mailing Liste?"

#: index.docbook:3407
msgid ""
"Well, there are more than one. Each focuses on a different aspect of &kde;. "
"Some of them are for the developers, so they are not discussed in detail. "
"Some of the more important lists that users might be interested in are:"
msgstr ""
"Es gibt mehrere. Jede hat einen anderen Schwerpunkt um &kde; herum. Einige "
"sind den Entwicklern vorbehalten, diese sind hier nicht im Detail "
"beschrieben. Einige der wichtigsten Listen sind:"

# index.docbook:3414, index.docbook:3414
#: index.docbook:3411
msgid "<term>kde</term>"
msgstr "<term>kde</term>"

#: index.docbook:3411
msgid "This is the main &kde; mailing list for general discussions."
msgstr "Dies ist die &kde;-Hauptmailingliste f&uuml;r generelle Diskussionen."

#: index.docbook:3411
msgid "kde-announce"
msgstr "kde-announce"

#: index.docbook:3411
msgid ""
"This list is used to announce new versions of &kde; as well as new tools and "
"applications."
msgstr ""
"Diese Liste wird zur Ank&uuml;ndigung von neuen Versionen von &kde; wie auch "
"von neuen Werkzeugen und Anwendungen benutzt."

#: index.docbook:3411
msgid "kde-user"
msgstr "kde-user"

#: index.docbook:3411
msgid "This list is intented for users helping other users."
msgstr "Hier helfen &kde;-Nutzer anderen &kde;-Nutzern."

#: index.docbook:3411
msgid "kde-look"
msgstr "kde-look"

#: index.docbook:3411
msgid ""
"This is the list that deals with questions of look and feel and general user "
"interface considerations."
msgstr ""
"Diese Liste behandelt Fragen des Erscheinungsbildes und generelle Fragen zur "
"Nutzeroberfl&auml;che."

#: index.docbook:3411
msgid "kde-licensing"
msgstr "kde-licensing"

#: index.docbook:3411
msgid ""
"This list is devoted to discussions about the &kde; and &Qt; license issues."
msgstr "Diese Liste ist Fragen der Lizensierung von &kde; und &Qt; gewidmet."

#: index.docbook:3433
msgid ""
"For the complete list of mailing lists available, please refer to <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kde.org/contact.html\">http://www.kde.org/contact.html</ulin"
"k>."
msgstr ""
"Eine komplette Liste der vorhandenen Mailinglisten finden Sie unter: <ulink "
"url=\"http://www.kde.org/contact.html\">http://www.kde.org/contact.html</ulin"
"k>."

#: index.docbook:3436
msgid ""
"Please note that it is not a good idea to ask questions which are already "
"answered in this <acronym>FAQ</acronym>."
msgstr ""
"Beachten Sie bitte, dass es als unh&ouml;flich angesehen wird, wenn sie in "
"Mailinglisten Fragen stellen, die in einer <acronym>FAQ</acronym> "
"beantwortet werden."

#: index.docbook:3443
msgid "How do I subscribe/unsubscribe to these lists?"
